value.0: Fine Jorian is a fine man and a skilled merchant.
He likes his cloak, so don't make fun of it.
This suit identifies you as an Amian Trader.

Artificer Theoric is without question the most capable smith the City of Light has known for generations. He is no man of great theological knowledge and has no skill in holding sermons, but his work with the hammer and anvil has earned him great respect among fellow artisans of the city-state. His works are sought by anyone who understands the trade and tend to fetch unrivaled prices on the market.

Value.value: *he wipes his brow* Time for work. Glad to be back in business. Make sure to stop by and see our merchants' wares!

value.0: The Fort Cystana Silver Dragon guards serve and protect the people, acting as the first line of defense against would-be villains and criminals.

Value.value: Have a look around. We have arms and armor, a fletcher, and room for you to sell your own wares, if you like.

Value.value: We're still furnishing the place, but it's looking good in here.

value.0: This dwarf has had a long-standing rivalry with Fine Jorian, but during the peoples' trying times, the pair formed an unbreakable bond. Now this dwarf is a business partner, sharing everything with his human smith friend.

A rather plump individual, Rachel acts much like a mother to the younger mages - whether they like it or not! She also tends the mythal forge.

Value.value: Yes! This is perfect! Er... Flawless, I mean! Thank you very much. Here's the Enhanced Recall Stone, as promised. My associate will tell you more about these stones, if you like.

I am looking for Flawless Mythals for my research into the events which led to the creation of the crystals. In exchange, I offer a valuable Enhanced Recall Stone, which you can use in addition to the usual Recall Stones. I'll exchange as many times as you want!
